SEPTEMBER 6
PHIL. HISTORY
                                                                                                                                 In 1955, a better trade Agreement between the Philippines and the United States was signed.

This was through the Laurel-Langley Agreement following the conclusion of negotiations between Senator Jose Laurel and diplomat James Langley in December, 1954.

The agreement replaced the Bell Trade Act which was unpopular among Filipinos due to its provisions that tied the Philippine economy to the US.
It abolished the US authority to control the exchange rate of the peso and the made the parity privileges reciprocal. The agreement expired in 1974

PRAYER FOCUS
May trade agreements between the Philippines and other countries be truly favorable to the Filipinos. May our diplomats and representatives to these agreements be nationalistically wise and persuasive, and attempts by foreigners to deceive and manipulate us be thwarted by them

 Unity and win-win agreements must be maintained by Christians
