SEPTEMBER 7
PHIL. HISTORY
                                                                                                                                 In 1974, the Pantabangan Dam in Nueva Ecija was formally opened.
                                                                                                               Construction of this multi-purpose, P800 M-worth dam begun in June, 1971. That’s after the Philippine Congress authorized the development of the Pampanga Basin through Rep. Act 5499, which led to the thorough study and plan of the said dam.
                                                                                                                        Owned by the National Power Corporation, this dam provides water for irrigating farms and hydro electric power generation. It’s reservoir, Pantabangan Lake, affords flood control.

PRAYER FOCUS
May this and the rest of our dams be protected from natural disasters and man-made destructions. May these produce ample hydro electric power and water for irrigation. May the government find more sources of alternative energy.
                                                                                                                              The Holy Spirit’s power is the best source of spiritual water and energy

Whoever believes in me, as Scripture has said, rivers of living water will flow from within them.”[c] 39 By this he meant the Spirit, whom those who believed in him were later to receive. – John 7:38b-39
