SEPTEMBER 8
PHIL. HISTORY
                                                                                                                                 In 1954, the Southeast Asia Treaty Organization was established in Manila

Also known as the Manila Pact, it aimed to stop the spread of communism in the region. Its founding members were the Philippines, United States, France, Australia, United Kingdom, New Zealand, Pakistan and Thailand
                                                                                                                              The organization held joint military training yearly, and had some work on mutual social and economic concerns. It disbanded in June, 1977. It was later replaced with the ASEAN, or Association of South East Asian Nations.
                                                                                                                        PRAYER FOCUS:
May the ASEAN and other regional and global associations continue to develop good relationships with other member-countries.  May the ASEAN unite strongly against any abuse of powerful countries like China especially regarding the West Phil. Seas.

Treaty or no treaty, the key to peaceful alliances between people and countries are basic
