SEPTEMBER 8
WORLD HISTORY
                                                                                                                                 In 1945, U.S. troops arrived in Korea to begin its occupation of the country’s southern part.
                                                                                                                              This was in line with the Allied Forces post war agreement (US, USSR, China & Great Britain) to liberate the Koreans from the Japanese Imperial Army which had possessed their land since early 20th Century.
                                                                                                                              The agreement included that the Russians will in turn occupy Korea’s northern part. Once both parts were totally liberated from the Japanese, US and Russian forces would leave to facilitate the unification of an independent Korea

 This didn’t happen. After the Russians left in 1948 and the Americans went home in 1949, communist North Koreans invaded their southern counterparts.
That forced the US to return and secure the territory of the south, That kept Korea divided until now.

 PRAYER FOCUS
May the unification process of these two countries succeed eventually. Meanwhile, may military and political confrontation be prevented always
                                                                                                                             May we all realize and experience the glory of unifying with our brethren
                                                                                                                             How good and pleasant it is when God’s people live together in unity!  - Psalm 133:1